# Morse Keyer Custom License

**Notice regarding Source-Available Status:**  
Morse Keyer is distributed as **Source-Available** software. This license is intentionally more restrictive than standard Open Source Initiative (OSI) definitions. The explicit restriction on commercial use is designed in favor of radio amateurs and enthusiasts, guaranteeing that this community project cannot be hijacked whether for profit or not while allowing the Original Developer to sustain the project's long-term development and centralize community improvements for the benefit of all users.

In this license, "**Original Developer**" refers to Luis Quesada Torres, and "**Original Code**" or "**Original Application**" refers to the Morse Keyer software as maintained at https://github.com/lquesada/MorseKeyer.

This software can be modified and shared under the following conditions:

1. **Attribution**: If a binary or a modified version is shared, it must be shared with references to the original developer and this repository (https://github.com/lquesada/MorseKeyer). Additionally, all modified versions must:
    - Clearly state that they are a "modified version of Morse Keyer" in the credits, app description, repository, and any other public-facing documentation.
    - Include a prominent link to https://github.com/lquesada/MorseKeyer.
2. **Source Code Distribution**: If the binary contains modified code, the whole modified source code of this app, together with building scripts and any components necessary to make it run, must be made publicly available under this exact same license (for example, via a public GitHub repository).
3. **No Commercial Applications**: You cannot resell this application, nor applications that use code from this application (either original or modified), and you cannot bundle the application in a device or preinstall it in a device and sell the device. What is acceptable is to point users to the webpage or Google Play Store to install the application.

If you want a commercial licensing deal, you must reach out to the **Original Developer**. Commercial licensing deals will only be granted under conditions that explicitly safeguard the interests of the community. Only the **Original Code** or **Original Application** can be subject to commercial license deals, provided the **Original Developer** agrees. Any modified code or versions of this application cannot be commercialized, and no extra license agreements can be made on them.

**Back-contribution.**
If you modify this software and publish the modified version or its source code, you hereby grant the Original Developer the right to incorporate any of your improvements, changes, and modifications back into the Original Code or Application and any future versions thereof, including the right for the Original Developer to license such integrated work under commercial terms in accordance with the "No Commercial Applications" section above, always with due credit and reference to your contribution.

